    "body": "```\r\n$ ./bin/spack install pflotran@xsdk-0.2.2\r\n==> Error: Class constructor failed for package 'pflotran'.\r\n\r\nCaused by:\r\nNoURLError: Package Pflotran has no version with a URL.\r\n  File \"/Users/barrysmith/Src/spack/lib/spack/spack/repository.py\", line 579, in get\r\n    self._instances[key] = package_class(copy)\r\n  File \"/Users/barrysmith/Src/spack/lib/spack/spack/package.py\", line 564, in __init__\r\n    f = fs.for_package_version(self, self.version)\r\n  File \"/Users/barrysmith/Src/spack/lib/spack/spack/fetch_strategy.py\", line 898, in for_package_version\r\n    url = pkg.url_for_version(version)\r\n  File \"/Users/barrysmith/Src/spack/lib/spack/spack/package.py\", line 684, in url_for_version\r\n    raise NoURLError(cls)\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhy are you forcing me to provide a \"url\" when my only distribution mechanism is git? This use to work fine.",
